    <p class="section-number">Why we get called back</p>
    <h2>What separates our grill service from general appliance repair.</h2>

    <ul class="reasons-list">
      <li><strong>Brand expertise.</strong> Lynx vs Fire Magic vs DCS: different ignition systems, different burner architectures, different parts. Most "appliance repair" companies don't know which is which.</li>
      <li><strong>Parts on the van.</strong> Lynx spark modules, 9V and AAA batteries, Fire Magic hot-surface igniters, common DCS radiants, Twin Eagles glow rods, regulators for the top six brands.</li>
      <li><strong>Coastal salt expertise.</strong> Malibu, Newport Beach, Pacific Palisades calls are about 35% of our grill work. We know which parts fail near saltwater.</li>
      <li><strong>Honest replace-vs-repair.</strong> A 14-year-old grill with a $1,800 burner kit failure may not be worth fixing. We'll say so.</li>
      <li><strong>EPA 608.</strong> Covers the few outdoor grills with refrigerated drawers integrated into the cabinet.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 plus BBB A+.</strong> Verifiable with the state and the bureau.</li>
